cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it using these metadata."
title: "ScatterBootstrap: Small-angle scattering model fitting with bootstrap-based uncertainty quantification"
abstract: >-
  A Python package for fitting small-angle X-ray and neutron scattering (SAXS/SANS)
  data with high-performance C form factor and structure factor models and for
  quantifying parameter uncertainties via residual bootstrapping.
authors:
  - family-names: Kaufmann
    given-names: Tobias
    affiliation: "ETH Zürich"
